 Why does Trump want Greenland?

305
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:56,500
 And could he get it?

306
00:24:56,500 --> 00:25:03,500
 Yeah, I think, you know, he's a real estate guy, likes to acquire real estate.

307
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:10,500
 But the only way he would get it would be to, quote, buy it from Denmark, and I don't think Denmark's selling.

308
00:25:11,500 --> 00:25:23,500
 I think the most likely outcome is the people of Greenland will declare their own independence from Denmark and become their own territory, their own country.

309
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:26,500
 And then they'll negotiate a treaty with the United States.

310
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:28,500
 But here's the problem.

311
00:25:28,500 --> 00:25:39,500
 Trump is asserting that he wants Greenland because Greenland is a bridge to the Arctic and the perceived riches that are to be had in the Arctic.

312
00:25:40,500 --> 00:25:44,500
 Well, the question is, how's the U.S. going to get there?

313
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:49,500
 Because they're not going to strap on snowshoes and walk across the ice.

314
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:56,500
 Now, the United States right now has one ship that is an icebreaker.

315
00:25:56,500 --> 00:25:58,500
 Only one.

316
00:25:58,500 --> 00:25:59,500
 They used to have two.

317
00:25:59,500 --> 00:26:00,500
 The other one caught on fire.

318
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:05,500
 Russia, by contrast, has 70 icebreakers.

319
00:26:06,500 --> 00:26:10,500
 And of those 70, seven of them are nuclear powered.

320
00:26:10,500 --> 00:26:18,500
 Russia is already in the Arctic, has been in the Arctic, has a presence because it can sail there.

321
00:26:18,500 --> 00:26:23,500
 It can put people on board ships and move there with no problem.

322
00:26:24,500 --> 00:26:25,500
 The United States can't.

323
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:35,500
 The United States has no ability right now to project any kind of force or presence into the Arctic region.

324
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:44,500
 And even if they get special access to Greenland, everything they do is still going to have to be done from Greenland as a land base.

325
00:26:45,500 --> 00:26:50,500
 Because the United States lacks the power to project any kind of force on the maritime front.

326
00:26:50,500 --> 00:26:53,500
 So there's talk about Canada too.

327
00:26:53,500 --> 00:26:57,500
 What do Americans think about all these ideas?

328
00:26:58,500 --> 00:27:00,500
 Well, we've been invaded by...

329
00:27:00,500 --> 00:27:07,500
 You know, I live down in Florida and every winter we get invaded by all the folks from Canada, particularly from Quebec.

330
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:11,500
 The Quebecois, you know, the ones that parlez-vous français.

331
00:27:11,500 --> 00:27:20,500
 But taking on Canada, I'm not even sure nobody's even thought through how that would work.

332
00:27:21,500 --> 00:27:32,500
 If Canada is the 51st state, they only get two senators and maybe each of the different provinces would give the different additional votes to the House of Representatives.

333
00:27:32,500 --> 00:27:38,500
 Well, you're bringing in a country that's more likely to vote with the Democrats than with the Republicans.

334
00:27:38,500 --> 00:27:48,500
 So that would be stupid on Trump's part to, you know, bring in his own self-destruction from within.

335
00:27:49,500 --> 00:27:55,500
 I think all of this was nothing more than just Donald Trump tweaking the nose of the Canadian leadership.

336
00:27:55,500 --> 00:27:56,500
 So he was trolling.

337
00:27:56,500 --> 00:27:58,500
 He was trolling.

338
00:27:58,500 --> 00:27:59,500
 Absolutely.

339
00:27:59,500 --> 00:28:03,500
 Mr. Johnson, are Americans tired of wars?

340
00:28:03,500 --> 00:28:04,500
 Yes.

341
00:28:04,500 --> 00:28:06,500
 Yeah, very much so.

342
00:28:06,500 --> 00:28:12,500
 And that's where, you know, Trump's rhetoric is, hey, I'm going to keep us out of needless wars.

343
00:28:12,500 --> 00:28:17,500
 And yet they're talking about, oh, I'll go to war with China, go to war with Iran.

344
00:28:18,500 --> 00:28:29,500
 I've said it before, and I will reiterate it, that if Donald Trump gets embroiled in wars, he will be destroying his presidency.

345
00:28:30,500 --> 00:28:47,500
 If he goes through his term without embroiling the United States in another war and achieves peaceful relations with Russia and with China and with Iran, he will go down in history as maybe the greatest president ever.

346
00:28:48,500 --> 00:28:49,500
 So, it's really in his hands.

347
00:28:49,500 --> 00:28:50,500
 It's really in his hands.

348
00:28:50,500 --> 00:28:53,500
 And he's got the, he's got the control over it.

349
00:28:53,500 --> 00:28:54,500
 It remains to be seen what he does.

350
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:56,500
 Yes.

351
00:28:56,500 --> 00:28:59,500
 Uh, are warmongers still active?

352
00:28:59,500 --> 00:29:01,500
 We all know that war is big business.

353
00:29:01,500 --> 00:29:03,500
 Yeah.

354
00:29:03,500 --> 00:29:05,500
 So, will the neocons calm down now?

355
